% causes a first set of the data elements having incoming existence headers to
% be deemed to exist and a second set of the data elements having outgoing
% existence headers to be deemed to not exist."
% Claim 3 recites that the existence group maintains a list of outgoing headers
% and a list of incoming headers; claim 4 recites the post-flip cleanup walk
